== Cook the potatoes ==

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the oven to 375 degrees. Peel and dice the @russet potatoes{24%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch cubes. Place them in a #medium pot{} with enough water to cover and @salt{large pinch}. Bring to a boil and cook for ~{12-15%minutes}, until fork-tender. Drain, reserving 1⁄4 cup of the potato water.

== Prep the ingredients ==

Halve, peel, and mince the @shallots{2}. Mince or grate the @garlic{4%cloves}. Finely chop the @chives{1/2%ounce}.

== Form the turkey meatballs ==

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the @ground turkey{16%ounce}, @panko breadcrumbs{1/2%cup}, @Italian seasoning{2%teaspoon}, half the shallot, and half the garlic. Season with @salt{1%teaspoon} and @pepper{}. Form the mixture into golf ball-sized meatballs.

== Cook the meatballs ==

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Working in batches, if necessary, add the meatballs to the pan and cook for ~{1-2%minutes} per side, rotating to brown on all sides. Transfer the meatballs to a #baking sheet{} and place them in the oven for ~{5-6%minutes}, or until cooked through.

== Mash the potatoes ==

Heat @butter{2%tablespoon} in the same #pot{} you used for the potatoes over medium heat. Add the drained potatoes and chives and mash with a #fork{} or #potato masher{} until smooth. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and cover to keep warm.

> TIP: If the potatoes are too thick, add a splash of reserved potato water or milk.

== Make the creamed spinach ==

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in the same pan you used for the turkey meatballs over medium heat. Add the remaining garlic and shallot to the pan and cook for ~{1-2%minutes}, until softened. Scrape up any browned bits from the bottom of the pan. Add the @spinach{10%ounce} to the pan and toss for ~{2-3%minutes}, until wilted. Season with @salt{} and @white pepper{1%teaspoon}, to taste.

> TIP: You may need to add the spinach a little bit at a time so it will all fit in the pan.

Remove the pan from the heat and stir in half the @sour cream{1%ounce}. Remove the spinach from the pan and cover to keep warm.

== Reduce the sauce ==

Add the @veggie stock concentrate{2}, 1/2 cup water, and the remaining @sour cream{1%ounce} to the pan over medium heat. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer for ~{2-3%minutes}, until the sauce thickens.

== Finish and plate ==

Plate the turkey meatballs on a bed of chive-mashed potatoes and creamed spinach. Spoon the sauce over top and enjoy!